column5: Departed at 3:30 this morning and made the 1.5 hour drive . Knew they were calling for rain, but was still heading anyways. Get there, lake is nice and flat. Unload and fished for 3 hours. Lots of pound and a half fish. Lost a a nice tank. Knocked it off with the net. No matter, managed about 30 fish in the limited time. A few pics. Good mix bag lake. A fun lake to fish.    Just park and slip the toon in and go fishing. Everything on the white spinner bait. BOOYHA.
Beauty nice and simple, good day
Looks like a great few hours nice Brian

Thanks fellas.  Was well worth the early rise. I was to have breaky with the parents in the morning. Figured I had a few hours to get a fish in before then. Me pops an early riser aswell. I was on the lake at 5ish. He texted me at 5:30. Breaky is ready. LOL  He kept things warm til I got off the lake.
Beat the rain? The best fishing is in the rain!  Nicely done Brian
Beat the rain? The best fishing is in the rain!  Nicely done Brian  I forgot my bailing can Mike.
